<subSubSection id="26F76542FF9E463574A9FD6BFEA3FC62" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF9E463574A9FD6BFEE2FD81" blockId="2.[189,310,669,695]" box="[189,310,669,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="351A81A5FF9E463574A9FD6BFEE2FD81" bold="true" box="[189,310,669,695]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9E463574A9FD6BFEE2FD81" bold="true" box="[189,310,669,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF9E463574A9FD3BFEA3FC62" blockId="2.[188,1399,717,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Flowers with reduced, apically 3-lobed corona lobes. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF9E463577FFFD3BFBA8FDD0" box="[1003,1148,717,742]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9E463577FFFD3BFBA8FDD0" box="[1003,1148,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the acicular leaves, sessile cymes and urceolate corolla, internally bearded along the lobe basal half, but can be distinguished by the opposite leaves (vs verticillate in 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF9E46357724FCE0FC6DFC19" box="[816,953,790,815]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9E46357724FCE0FC6DFC19" box="[816,953,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and presence of a corona (vs absence in 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF9E463574CFFCCCFEB2FC65" box="[219,358,826,851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9E463574CFFCCCFEB2FC65" box="[219,358,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="26F76542FF9E463574A9FC8AFC1FFCF3" box="[189,971,892,966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF9E463574A9FC8AFE90FCA0" blockId="2.[189,324,892,918]" box="[189,324,892,918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
