</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF9E463574A9FC5DFC1FFCF3" blockId="2.[189,971,939,966]" box="[189,971,939,966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The epithet ʻ 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF9E46357547FC5DFE11FCF3" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[339,453,939,965]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9E46357547FC5DFE11FCF3" box="[339,453,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ refers to the apically 3-lobed corona lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
