<subSubSection id="26F76542FF99463274A9FEFEFCC4FD7A" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF99463274A9FEFEFD96FE15" blockId="5.[189,578,264,291]" box="[189,578,264,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading id="351A81A5FF99463274A9FEFEFD96FE15" bold="true" box="[189,578,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463274A9FEFEFD96FE15" bold="true" box="[189,578,264,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Provisional conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF99463274A9FECEFCC4FD7A" blockId="5.[188,1400,312,589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF99463274A9FECEFE14FE64" authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,448,312,338]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463274A9FECEFE14FE64" box="[189,448,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="47AA57A0FF99463275DDFECEFDF0FE64" box="[457,548,312,338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known from only two collections, both near the S„o Bento waterfall, in Chapada dos Veadeiros. Specimen labels provide no information about population density. However, the species is known to occur in a tourist location, surrounded by farms and cattle raising, has an area of occupancy (AOO) estimated at 
<quantity id="A9159B2CFF9946327648FE55FD4CFE8B" box="[604,664,419,445]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
<superScript id="99989B81FF994632768DFE54FD76FE86" attach="right" box="[665,674,418,432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">2</superScript>
, probably under continuing decline in geographic range and habitat quality. During fieldwork in the 
<typeStatus id="B156886BFF99463276B0FE31FD03FED7" box="[676,727,455,481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
locality, we did not find any specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF99463270C9FE31FAA2FED7" authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[1245,1398,455,481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463270C9FE31FAA2FED7" box="[1245,1398,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="47AA57A0FF99463274A9FE1DFECDFD33" box="[189,281,491,517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the new species has not been recollected since 1994. Based on criteria B2ab(i,ii,iii,iv) of the International Union for Conservation of Nature (
<bibRefCitation id="0A7C4B38FF994632770BFDF8FC7FFD1E" author="IUCN" box="[799,939,526,552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref4310" refString="IUCN. 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 14. IUCN, Gland / Cambridge." type="book" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
) Red List assessment, we provisionally classify the species as Critically Endangered (CR).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="26F76542FF99463274A9FD82FE19FC7A" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF99463274A9FD82FE50FDB8" blockId="5.[189,388,628,654]" box="[189,388,628,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading id="351A81A5FF99463274A9FD82FE50FDB8" bold="true" box="[189,388,628,654]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463274A9FD82FE50FDB8" bold="true" box="[189,388,628,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E5236C9FF99463274A9FD52FE19FC7A" blockId="5.[189,1399,675,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF99463274A9FD52FE14FD8B" authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,448,675,701]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463274A9FD52FE14FD8B" box="[189,448,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="47AA57A0FF99463275DDFD52FDF1FD88" box="[457,549,676,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has narrow leaves, urceolate corolla with bearded lobes and was found in a savannah of Central 
<collectingCountry id="16FA7659FF99463275F5FD31FDF8FDD7" box="[481,556,711,737]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Together, these features support its classification in 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF9946327085FD3EFACEFDD7" box="[1169,1306,712,737]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF9946327085FD3EFACEFDD7" box="[1169,1306,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="47AA57A0FF9946327135FD31FA8AFDD7" box="[1313,1374,711,737]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="A9ED4D4AFF99463275C2FD1DFDB5FC32" box="[470,609,747,772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis id="5C99EADBFF99463275C2FD1DFDB5FC32" box="[470,609,747,772]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the acicular leaves and sessile cymes, but differs from all other taxa in the genus by the opposite leaves and flowers with reduced corona lobes, as presented in the key below and 
<tableCitation id="236F0372FF994632757BFCC4FE13FC7A" box="[367,455,818,844]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="6.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Table 1. Diagnostic characters to distinguish the species of Hemipogon s. str." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3A926641FF9A463174A9FEFFFB92FE12" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" tableUuid="3A926641FF9A463174A9FEFFFB92FE12">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
